On May 11, 2019, Vice President Mike Pence delivered a commencement speech at Liberty University in Lynchburg, Virginia. He congratulated the graduating class of 2019 and spoke about the achievements of the university and its students. Pence highlighted the growing American economy, job opportunities, and the administration's efforts to protect religious freedom. He encouraged the graduates to live out their faith and be prepared to face opposition in a society that may not always tolerate traditional Christian beliefs. Pence concluded by urging the graduates to have faith in themselves, their principles, and in God as they go out into the world.